类 SpoutCollector<OUT>

    class SpoutCollector<OUT>
extends AbstractStormCollector<OUT>
implements org.apache.storm.spout.ISpoutOutputCollector
    A SpoutCollector is used by SpoutWrapper to provided an Storm compatible output collector to the wrapped spout. It transforms the emitted Storm tuples into Flink tuples and emits them via the provide SourceFunction.SourceContext object.

    • 构造器详细资料

      • SpoutCollector

        SpoutCollector(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> numberOfAttributes,
               int taskId,
               SourceFunction.SourceContext<OUT> flinkContext)
        throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
        Instantiates a new SpoutCollector that emits Flink tuples to the given Flink source context. If the number of attributes is specified as zero, any output type is supported. If the number of attributes is between 0 to 25, the output type is Tuple0 to Tuple25, respectively.
        参数:
        numberOfAttributes - The number of attributes of the emitted tuples.
        taskId - The ID of the producer task (negative value for unknown).
        flinkContext - The Flink source context to be used.
        抛出:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if the specified number of attributes is greater than 25
